1924;;The Red Lily;;American;;Fred Niblo;;Ramon Novarro, Enid Bennett;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Red_Lily;;Jean Leonnec (Ramon Novarro) and Marise La Noue (Enid Bennett) are penniless lovers who elope to Paris. However, they are separated shortly after their arrival, leading to a downward spiral in each of their lives. She becomes a prostitute known as 'the red lily'; he learns the ways of the underworld from Bo-Bo (Wallace Beery).